            <h3>Algorithm Competition Room 1 Summary</h3>
            <p>Posted May 13th 2008 4:03PM by <strong>Denis Horgan</strong></p>
            <p><strong><tc-webtag:handle coderId="15868491" darkBG="true" /> wins Room 1!</strong></p>
            <p>Algorithm Semifinal 1 opened the TCO'08 Algorithm Competition this morning. The round proved to be quite eventful. It started from many fast submissions on the 250, which was quite straightforward implementational problem. After this, nothing happened for a while. Most coders proceeded to the 500, but some skipped it to directly proceed to the 1000. <tc-webtag:handle coderId="144400" context="algorithm" darkBG="true" /> and <tc-webtag:handle coderId="22652597" context="algorithm" darkBG="true" /> even started the round with the 1000.</p>
